&lt;p&gt;The Technical Writing &amp;amp; Documentation team creates engaging and informative technical content, particularly our public product documentation: Datadog Docs. Our team is hands-on&amp;nbsp;with the technologies that Datadog monitors, and collaborates with technical and product teams&amp;nbsp;to create technical documentation for our APIs, SDKs, developer and security tools, and&amp;nbsp;community developed integrations — thousands of pages of content! Plus a monthly product&amp;nbsp;newsletter.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What You’ll Do: &amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Partner with our product and engineering teams, manage documentation projects, and create public user documentation, with a focus on Datadog Applied AI. Dig into source code for community and internally developed systems to collect technical details for documentation. &amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Create developer-facing documentation and guides for APIs, developer and SRE tools, and the Agent, to enable the developer and monitoring community to onboard and succeed with our products. &amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Collaborate with the docs team and our open source community to develop documentation standards and continually improve our processes. &amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;As a senior team member, you also provide coaching, mentoring, and guidance to others in the team. &amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Depending on the individual and team capacity, you may also contribute to our monthly newsletter, sent to over 500,000 customers per month. &amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Who You Are: &amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;You are an experienced technical writer with at least 5 years of relevant experience developing documentation with a developer or SRE audience, including SDK documentation. &amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;You are experienced in using Markdown, static-site generators, and Github to develop and publish documentation with a ‘Docs as Code’ approach. &amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;You are comfortable and familiar with using basic Python and reading at least 1 other programming language (e.g., Java, Ruby). &amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;You are comfortable and familiar with modern infrastructure such as IaaS cloud services and containers. &amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;You have publicly available technical writing samples. &amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;You have experience managing large and complex documentation sets and developing well-structured and effective information architecture. &amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Bonus points if you have experience with open source and partner ecosystem integrations and documentation development.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;Datadog values people from all walks of life. We understand not everyone will meet all the above qualifications on day one. That&#39;s okay. If you’re passionate about technology and want to grow your skills, we encourage you to apply. &amp;nbsp;&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Benefits and Growth: &amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;New hire stock equity (RSUs) and employee stock purchase plan (ESPP) &amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Continuous professional development, product training, and career pathing &amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Intradepartmental mentor and buddy program for in-house networking &amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;An inclusive company culture, ability to join our Community Guilds (Datadog employee resource groups) &amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Access to Inclusion Talks, our internal panel discussions &amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Free, global mental health benefits for employees and dependents age 6+ &amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Competitive global benefits&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;Benefits and Growth listed above may vary based on the country of your employment and the&amp;nbsp;nature of your employment with Datadog.&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
